<section class="py-5" style="background-color: #f9f7f1;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row align-items-center">
      
      <!-- LEFT SIDE: Image -->
      <div class="col-lg-5 text-center mb-4 mb-lg-0">
        <img src="./assests/hero1.png" 
             alt="Shilpashree T. Pankajaksha" 
             class="img-fluid rounded-4 shadow"
             style="max-height: 450px; object-fit: cover; background-color: whitesmoke;">
      </div>

      <!-- RIGHT SIDE: Text Content -->
      <div class="col-lg-7">
        <h2 class="fw-bold mb-3" 
            style="font-family: 'Marcellus', serif; color: #cba535;">
          About Shilpashree T. Pankajaksha
        </h2>
        <p class="lead" style="font-family: 'Great Victorian Standard', serif; color: #4a4a4a;">
          Born on 29th June 1971 and with formal school education in his hometown 
          Narasimharajapura in Karnataka, Mr. Pankajaksha had training in carpentry 
          (his family tradition). He later studied sculpture at the 
          K.P.J. Prabhu Artisan Training School at Bidadi in Karnataka. 
          His Shilpashastra training was under the internationally reputed 
          Prof. S.K. Ramachandra Rao — author of many books on different aspects of Indian culture.
        </p>
        <p class="lead" style="font-family: 'Great Victorian Standard', serif; color: #4a4a4a;">
          He has studied the four classical styles of sculpture — 
          <strong>Chalukya, Chera, Chola, and Hoysala</strong> — 
          and authored a book titled <em>“Shilpa Soundarya”</em> (in Kannada), 
          published by the Karnataka Shilpa Kala Academy, Bangalore.  
          He expresses gratitude for the assistance provided by the 
          <strong>India Foundation for the Arts</strong>, Bangalore, and the 
          <strong>Sir Ratan Tata Trust</strong>, Mumbai, established in 1919.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>


